ISLAMABAD, Jul 27 (APP): The Ministry of Law and Justice on Saturday issued the notification regarding the appointment of Mr. Justice Sardar Tariq Marood and Justice Mazhar Alam Khan Mandokhel as ad hoc judges of the Supreme Court of Pakistan.
The notification said, “The president of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan is pleased to appoint Mr. Justice Sardar Tariq Masood and Justice Mazhar Alam Khan Mandokhel, the former judges of Supreme Court, as ad hoc judges of the Supreme Court of Pakistan to attend the sittings of the court to a period of one year with effect from the date they enter upon their offices.”
